interfaces.label: ResolvedSimpleSavedObject
description:
This interface is a very simple wrapper for SavedObjects resolved from the server
with the {@link SavedObjectsClientContract}.

children.label: saved_object
description: The saved object that was found.

children.label: outcome
description:
The outcome for a successful `resolve` call is one of the following values:

 * `'exactMatch'` -- One document exactly matched the given ID.
 * `'aliasMatch'` -- One document with a legacy URL alias matched the given ID; in this case the `saved_object.id` field is different
   than the given ID.
 * `'conflict'` -- Two documents matched the given ID, one was an exact match and another with a legacy URL alias; in this case the
   `saved_object` object is the exact match, and the `saved_object.id` field is the same as the given ID.

children.label: alias_target_id
description:
The ID of the object that the legacy URL alias points to.

**Note:** this field is *only* included when an alias was found (in other words, when the outcome is `'aliasMatch'` or `'conflict'`).

children.label: alias_purpose
description:
The reason this alias was created.

Currently this is used to determine whether or not a toast should be shown when a user is redirected from a legacy URL; if the alias
was created because of saved object conversion, then we will display a toast telling the user that the object has a new URL.

**Note:** this field is *only* included when an alias was found (in other words, when the outcome is `'aliasMatch'` or `'conflict'`).

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsClientContract
description:
The client-side SavedObjectsClient is a thin convenience library around the SavedObjects
HTTP API for interacting with Saved Objects.

children.label: create
description: Creates an object

children.label: type
description: - the type of object to create

children.label: attributes
description: - the attributes of the object

children.label: options
description: {@link SavedObjectsCreateOptions }

returnComment: The result of the create operation - the created saved object

children.label: bulkCreate
description: Creates multiple objects at once

children.label: objects
description: - an array of objects containing type, attributes

children.label: options
description: {@link SavedObjectsBulkCreateOptions }

returnComment: The result of the create operation containing created saved objects.

children.label: delete
description: Deletes an object

children.label: type
description: - the type the of object to delete

children.label: id
description: - the id of the object to delete

children.label: options
description: {@link SavedObjectsDeleteOptions }

children.label: bulkDelete
description: Deletes multiple documents at once

children.label: objects
description: - an array of objects containing id, type

children.label: options
description: - optional force argument to force deletion of objects in a namespace other than the scoped client

returnComment: The bulk delete result for the saved objects for the given types and ids.

children.label: find
description: Search for objects

children.label: options
description: {@link SavedObjectsFindOptions }

returnComment: A find result with objects matching the specified search.

children.label: get

children.label: type

children.label: id

children.label: bulkResolve
description: Resolves an array of objects by id, using any legacy URL aliases if they exist

returnComment: The bulk resolve result for the saved objects for the given types and ids.

interfaces.label: SimpleSavedObject
description:
Very simple wrapper for SavedObjects loaded from the server
with the {@link SavedObjectsClientContract}.

It provides basic functionality for creating/saving/deleting saved objects,
but doesn't include any type-specific implementations.

children.label: id

children.label: error

children.label: references

children.label: updatedAt

children.label: createdAt

children.label: namespaces
